  "response": "Hillary Clinton chose Tim Kaine as her running mate in July 2016 after a careful vetting process. Kaine was seen as a pragmatic choice who could help her appeal to moderate voters and swing states. As a former Governor of Virginia and Senator, he had extensive political experience and was viewed as a safe, reliable pick. He was also seen as a strong complement to Clinton, with a reputation for being moderate and having good relationships across the political aisle. Kaine spoke Spanish and had done missionary work, which were additional qualities Clinton found appealing. While the exact details of her decision-making process are not fully public, these factors appeared to be key in her selection of Kaine as her vice presidential candidate.",
